               <p>JOHN MORGAN THOMAS. I am a <rs id="t18280911-212-viclabel1090" type="occupation">grocer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-212-victim1213 t18280911-212-viclabel1090"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18280911-212-crimeloc1091">High-street, Shadwell</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-212-crimeloc1091" type="placeName" value="High-street, Shadwell"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-212-crimeloc1091" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-212-off1088 t18280911-212-crimeloc1091"></join>. The prisoner came every day to my house to char, and was paid weekly; I lost three shillings from my till - she had access to that once a week, generally on the Monday or Tuesday. when she cleaned the shop. On the 12th of August I watched my till, which contained 2l. worth of silver and some copper; I placed myself in a sngar hogshead and heard the prisoner go to the till - I heard the money move; there was another person in the hogshead with me, and he could see through a hole what was done; I then went out and accused her of taking money - she said she had not; I sent for a constable, who found on her 3s. in silver, 8d. in copper, two 1/2lbs. and three 1/2lbs. of sugar, which I believe to be mine.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-212-person1214">
                  DAVID 
                  THOMAS
               <interp inst="t18280911-212-person1214" type="surname" value="THOMAS"></interp>
